Masivnější economic performance is reflected in the growing support for private business, and the market economy: approximately 71% of respondents across the entire area, says that private enterprise is necessary for the development of, this percentage has increased from 56% from the year 2007 (see Figure 6).
Some 58% agrees that a market economy is only system that will allow the development of their country, this percentage has increased from 47% from last year.
Interestingly, 62% of respondents in Venezuela is of the same opinion (and 80% there supports private enterprise), even though their leftist president Hugo Chávez expropriating many private firms.
