He tiptoed to the center
In the weeks, when suddenly widowed, benefiting Cristina Ferndndez, Argentina 's president, from the public sympathy, when its popularity increased from 20% to more than 50%, the highest level since it was in the year 2007 elected.
Yet the reversal of this success in the successful campaign for a second term in elections in the next year may depend on the mourners Mrs Fernándezová relinquishes nekompromisnosti my late husband, predecessor and political partner Néstora Kirchner.
And on these characteristics are all based.
Mr. Kirchner, who continued in economic policy and, after his wife successfully became president, was in the habit of budgeting, which downgrading tax revenues, economic growth and inflation.
This allowed the first pair spend more revenue at will.
