The budget for the year 2010 will now also apply to the next year, while the president will have more room to spend at will.
The economy is overheating excessively: this year 's likely growth to 9%.
Oficiální inflation rate is now at 11.1%, but many private estimates and trade unionists speaks of heading, which are close to 30%.
Mr. Kirchner, which took office in 2003, when Argentina was plagued by economic collapse, established a priority for growth and poverty reduction, rather than on controlling inflation.
Has refused to deal with the IMF, with the private sector and cleaned INDEC, statistical agency, which has acceded to monitor the inflationary official statistics.
It may now, the president of the Fernándezová moderated this policy?
Called for negotiations between private enterprises and trade union leaders.
And its officials say that they want to in the next year to limit the wage growth on 18%.
The economy was supported by the growth in world prices for exports argentine agricultural products.
But inflation impeding growth, based on a big depreciation in 2002.
This may be the reason why Mrs. President Fernándezová suggests that he wants to restore Argentina 's financial ties to the rest of the world.
Earlier this year, the government has created an agreement with the bondholders, who had refused to debt restructuring, which Argentina in 2001 did not pay.
Now faces Mrs. President Fernándezová agreement with the creditor governments, which are grouped in the Paris Club, which he owes roughly 6,7 billion.
