The lion 's again ready to cry now, when the restructuring MGM obtained from the final approval
After 18 months shocks and uncertainty got MGM finally the green light to start again.
A federal judge Insolvent New York on Thursday officially blessed `` pre - packaged "plan creditors settle about 5 billion of debt and clear the way for 86 years old entertainment company, which focuses on the production and production of the film and television show.
Thursday 's decrees that plan meets the requirements of the Insolvency Statute of the US do not remain MGM no legal impediments to reignite the founder of the Spyglass Entertainment Gary Barber and Roger Birnbaum, who become the main leading zeštíhleného study.
The number of employees falls on roughly 320 from more than 400.
MGM emerge suddenly from chapter 11, until the JP Morgan Chase agrees on the planned financial resources to enable the loan of EUR 500 million to finance new operations and production MGM.
Now is to link with the investment bank, which itself needs to 75 million dollars and funding is expected to be about half of December.
The restructuring process began to study in May 2009, which was hired the investment bank Moelis &amp; Co. to advise the management, how to solve your finances, since the Management fought to could afford interest payments of 300 million dollars a year.
The August was the President Harry Sloan replaced by Stephen Cooper, a former Director General Enron and an expert on turnover, known to his work for a Krispy Kreme Doughnuts.
Attempts to Moelise and Cooper to resolve the financial trouble MGM and 140 creditors study took longer than expected.
After a few months of discussions with the parties agree that, at the end of the year 2009 the company to put up for sale.
Although the auction attracted a few bidders, none of them were willing to pay $2 billion plus funds, which demanded creditors.
In the spring of this year, it was all back to the drawing board and team MGM began working on the restructuring plan. after months of faint bell and internal dissensions plan was creditor ultimately approved at the end of October.
When MGM in the coming weeks, officially will rise from bankruptcy, firms Moelise and Cooper receives for his work multimillion - dollar bonuses in dollars.
The company Moelis &amp; Co., which has already received 1,2 million dollars, he will receive the payment of 9,5 million.
Cooperovy firms that collected for its services, which runs the company, 375 000 dollars a month, a reward for success, the so - called `` success "fee 4 million dollars.
The Barber and Birnbaum plans to restore the production in MGM, which in this year, the only one film and put together a proposal to seven or eight films, which will emerge at the beginning of the year 2012.
They are also to participate in the financing of two films, which will be the subject of a book `` the hobbit, "and that, together with Warner Bros.
Studio needs to negotiate a special loan between 265 million and $275 million dollars to zafinancovalo its share of these two movies, which is going to Peter Jackson.
The investor Carl Icahn, which owns about 18% of the debt MGM sought to merge the companies Lions Gate Entertainment, in which is the largest shareholder.
However, the recent discussions between the two companies did not result in the agreement.
