Veterans of the Khmer Rouge are forced to come to terms with the past
In the dimly lit room with a concrete zašpiněnými and oloupanými walls reminded the headmaster Anlong Veng High School of a man who built it, the leader of the Khmer Rouge the fluid.
`` We all love the Mocha. "
`` It was a good leader and took care of his people, "said Sreng KOR, Ma, 42.
Known as `` the butcher "for his brutality during the Khmer Rouge, remains commander in this remote estate Khmer Rouge in the northwest Cambodia popular, where he built the hospital, bridges, and other infrastructure, and where is still alive thousands of former soldiers of this organization.
But this year, 12 years after the Khmer Rouge gave governments, she 's busted long - lasting loyalty also in Anlong Vengu.
In April were victims at the Forum truth and reconciliation allowed to publicly to confront with people who were part of the regime.
In June, the government has provided textbooks, which for the first time children to explain the history of the Khmer Rouge and their former soldiers.
And in July, raise together the UN, and Cambodia 's Court first conviction of the former member of the Khmer Rouge, the judgment of the former leader, the notoriously famous thuggish associations Tuol Sleng, Kaing Khek Iev, known as a ghost, to 35 years in prison.
With each step forward, increasing restlessness between veterans of the Khmer Rouge in Anlong Veng, which complicates the efforts of reconciliation and their attempts to engage in Cambodia 's company.
`` Between the former Khmer Rouge 's hatred and fear, but they are helpless to do anything, "said Youk Chhang, head of the documentation centre Cambodia, an independent organization, which explores the regime.
`` For them, life was between the Khmer Rouge a beautiful, but the regime has become a symbol of evil. "
`` Divides that family. "
During the Khmer Rouge in Cambodia, since 1975 in 1979, was estimated 1,7 million people executed, or died of starvation, on a disease or reprocessing.
When the Vietnamese attacked to overthrow the government, Pol Pot in 1979, the remains of the regime and its soldiers fled to the cambodian border with Thailand.
There was a rebellion, which lasted until the last movement in December 1998.
Pol Pot, Nuon Chea and Ieng Sary guided the guerrilla war of their bases in the mountains and the jungles in Western Cambodia, while the fluid cultivated supporters in Anlong Vengu.
But in the mid - 1990 's, after a peace agreement, sponsored by the UN, the country was led to the first democratic elections in 1993. of a large group of the warriors of the Khmer Rouge began to pace to the government, which culminated in the surrender Ieng Sary in 1996 and Nuon Chea and Khieu Samphan in 1998.
Pol Pot died of natural causes in 1998, and the fluid, which persisted, was in 1999, was captured by the government forces in the mountains nedalých Dangrek.
He died in Phnom Penhském prison in 2006, while waiting for the process.
Their patrons of them nepečovali, most of the former combatants Khmer Rouge sunk to ordinary Cambodia 's rural life, and many of them nostalgically recalled for a period of movement.
Although several elite of the Khmer Rouge maintain its local government position in exchange for their weapons, their position remains weak, as unskilled farmers.
`` Such people from the surrender of a minimum of, "said rival Leang of the Center for Justice and reconciliation, which is a public forum for the whole of Cambodia, including Anlong Vengu.
`` They are surrounded by utopian agrarian ideology mode. "
`` They were manners, without any ideas about the implementation of the trade. "
SOR Lim, 55, which came to the Khmer Rouge as a teenager in 1974, fought in the jungle around Anlong Vengu before settled as poor farmers in 1998.
`` Life under the Khmer Rouge was good, "he said.
`` The fluid all living. "
`` But now is hard life, because all we must ensure themselves. "
The court of the Khmer Rouge also raised concerns.
At the beginning of the next year will begin to court to investigate Nuon Chea, Khieu Samphan, Ieng Sary and his wife, Ieng Thirith, a former minister of the Khmer Rouge.
The court 's mandate to prosecute heads of přestavitele and the people responsible for the crimes, but it was not speaking, whether it will continue also in the four cases.
It was just a few to reassure concerns in Anlong Vengu.
The recent speculation media attention to the IM Chaema, 64, which was a district leader in the province of Banteay Meanchey during the Khmer Rouge at the end of the 1970 s.
In 2007, say researchers from the documentation centre in Cambodia, keeping an eye on the construction of dams Trapeang Thma, project, which may have been killed thousands of compulsory workers.
The recent upon the evening, the IM Chae returned from work in the field to his wooden cottage in dirty way out of Anlong Veng.
As the sun began to descend and there were shadows across the parched grass, IM Chae refused to speak about his past between the Khmer Rouge.
If the court called refused to go.
`` In Cambodia of peace and is a stable, "she said.
`` If they appear further prosecution, there will be war. "
Prime Minister Hun Sen that ran from the Khmer Rouge in 1978, too, has repeatedly warned that occurs to instability, if the court to search for more suspects, although the experts and historians disagree.
`` Cambodia must dig a deep hole and buried in the past, "he said.
But confrontation with the past is only what must Cambodia do to move forward, said Youk Chhang from the documentation centre.
`` The reconciliation in khmerským emoluments means cobble together the broken pieces, "he said.
`` It is our duty to give the broken pieces together, so that we could understand. "
The center has made the first book approved by the government on the Khmer Rouge, has 75 parties and the name `` history of democratic Cambodia. "
