Belarus agrees that seems to their weapons stocks on the basis of uranium
In a startling victory in the campaign President Obama 's on ensuring nuclear material around the world, announced Belarus government in the center of abandoning its stocks of highly enriched uranium, which is a critical component of nuclear weapons.
The agreement was published in a joint statement issued for the safety of the summit Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton and the belarusian Foreign Minister Sergei Martynovem.
The US government for years trying to convince Belarus, in order to surrender of highly enriched uranium, and seemed to the worst hit last spring.
But the US officials said the Washington Post, that in the last two months, it was with Belarus carried out a couple of classified operations to eliminate 187 pounds of uranium weapons on the basis of the research facility.
I have paved the way for the Wednesday agreement to remove the rest of the material - about 500 pounds, according to an official, who spoke under the condition of anonymity, because it is a sensitive issue.
The agreement has turned out to be one of the most important of the results of the Obama 47. national summit on nuclear safety in April, on which was Belarus scrapped.
And he was probably a good move to ensure the invitation of the former soviet republics at the summit in 2012.
`` I was really fascinated by the fact that they want to place at the summit on nuclear safety 2012. "
`` It shows that process works, "Ken said Luongo, president of the Partnership for global security, support groups nuclear safety.
Clinton called the agreement as `` very important, an important step "from Belarus.
Obama has promised in Prague in April 2009, by ensuring that all sensitive nuclear materials around the world to four years.
Since then, the US government has helped the six countries get rid of all their stocks of highly enriched uranium.
Belarus will be the seventh.
A dozen countries do so for the management of George W. Bush.
At the time of the Obama summit on nuclear safety announced Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko, that his people will never give up its uranium.
`` We are highly enriched uranium - hundreds of pounds of what is essentially the basis for the gun and less enriched uranium, "he said then Lukashenko.
`` It 's our commodity... do not intend to produce dirty bomb, and it is not to sell. "
`` We use it only for research purposes, that 's all. "
Belarus, however, a few months ago acceded to the United States and made clear interest to reach an agreement.
The first commitment to remove the belarusian uranium in October, was particularly difficult, because the material was slightly irradiated, officials announced.
He was loaded onto the special train, who toured the more than 300 miles into Russia 's facilities for the storage and disposal, officials said.
Second operation was concluded on Monday and was carried out by air, officials said.
The US government for the programme spent 13 million, most of it to the supply of belarusian Research Institute less enriched uranium, for the manufacture of nuclear weapons.
`` It was all zkoordinováno very carefully and managed on the basis of trust ," which led to the agreement signed by the Clinton, said Andrew Bieniawski, an official of the Department of Energy working for the Global Threat Reduction effort.
James Martin Center for the study of the Non - Proliferation Treaty this year estimated that Belarus has at least 88 pounds of uranium applicable for weapons production.
Belarus is, according to the joint declaration, seek to eliminate their stocks in 2012.
Relations between Belarus and the United States have been over the years of tense, primarily because of Lukašenkově violent repression of human rights.
But the Wednesday declaration suggests the possibility of gradual melting.
`` We welcome progress in these global security issues, the United States, and Belarus acknowledge that greater respect for democracy and human rights in Belarus remains the basis of the improved relations, and it is necessary for the progress of the country and its people, "he said.
