The Red Bull imitates Formula 1 with a secret weapon from Siemens
Software proposes improvement in vehicles in real time.
From the moment of the Red Bull barge in the series Formula 1 in 2004, its history in this exceptional world speed is characterised by surprise and success.
Initially, could not too seriously options for this the newcomer 's team, and despite the upward trend of late, all bets were on the triumph of Ferrari Fernando Alonsa.
But without reducing riding ability to champion, the Germans Sebastian Vettela, or the possibility of engine Renault, the power of his car, in a world in which the legend - `` secret weapon ," multi - ethnic Siemens put into the hands of the Red Bullu him to do so the winning team.
In fact, it is the Executive Software simulate thought that the german company said on the market in 2007 for the purposes of the very distant automotive sport.
The so - called plm, this powerful software apparatus, had been used to design assembly lines in manufacturing plants throughout the world, in energy plants and for the instrument with high precision.
Its aim is faithfully reproduced product or simulate the process of earlier than is created, thereby to avoid unnecessary mistakes and spending.
Plm would facilitate the development of the camera CANON, aircraft Sukhoi or the commercial vehicles brands Nissan.
Siegfried Russwurm, leading industrial division of the company 's Siemens, explains that the use of this software instruments to the Red Bull take place in a few hours, almost in real time "modification and improvement, which otherwise would detect during the factories and the tests.
Russwurm says that in 1992, employing the stables on average 10 technicians who are able to make a maximum of three or four improvement during a period.
In the Red Bull works today to 180 junior high - skilled professionals with executive information technology, who analyzed and propose any type of modification racing cars.
The Head of Siemens explained that the software plm is unable to analyze and improve all the elements of racing cars Red Bull, with the exception of the engine, which is entirely responsible Renault.
Modify the materials, fuel, aerodynamics and security features.
Changes can be converted from the virtual reality, in fact, during the less than 24 hours through advanced by using the laser systems and high - tech Autoclave.
The only limit of this technical advances is the amount of $40 million representing the maximum, which may each team Formula 1 issue for each period to improve its competitiveness.
The Red Bull has set up roughly 50 km from London race - technology used to design and manufacturing his racing cars.
This is the two buildings, which is limited by the entry visits - especially journalists.
What is happening here, is considered a `` great secret ."
List of interested in this project has 580 persons, including two pilots - champion Vettela and Mark Webber.
A hero of the Red Bullu 's Formula 1, without a doubt fresh champion Sebastian Vettel.
For the fathomless technological means that the energy of drinks channeled to its participation in the racing circuits, but there are other protagonists, whose aid is priceless, and there is no one knows.
The head of the production technology Steve Nevey argue that five years ago, it was possible to say that the advances in research and development of vehicles to contribute to the victory of 50%, and the rest was the result of the riders.
Currently, the ratio is changed and technology is behind the successes of 85%, while the pilots contribute from 15%.
Nevey acknowledges that Vettel or Webber will never be replaced by computer technology, since it is the `` unpredictable Gladiators ."
