China 's compliance with its target to reduce greenhouse gases
The representative of the country 's at the UN Conference on climate change the COP 16 assured that his country has developed a special efforts to reduce carbon footprint, and adds that insists on its promise to reduce by 2020 greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45%.
China follows through on its promise to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45% in the year 2020, assured Su Wei, a representative of the country 's at the UN Conference on climate change.
In its first public appearance on the 16 th Conference of the parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change Su Wei assured that his country has made an effort to reduce carbon footprint and turned its industry.
He said that his country during the last four years already invested $245 million in the effort to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
Make, however, that China will not change their objectives and will be on this matter to continue, together with the international community work.
Reported that China 's strategy in matters of climate change is divided into the following four items: a dialogue capacity building, the institution building and support pilot programmes.
In all of these points already experienced progress, which includes the last year 's approval of a new law on energy, which includes the proposed targets for reducing greenhouse gas emissions, explained.
Furthermore, he pointed out that in China cooperated federal authorities in a coordinated way with the authorities provincial and local, in order to achieve its objectives, in terms of energy saving energy efficiency and reduce emissions.
Moreover, as said, are in operation or had already been completed the various plans for several years, which are financed as the Chinese Government, as well as other governments.
For example, the case, he said, the programme for the efficient use of energy, which was introduced during the last five years, and who received an investment from the UN, the government and private initiative.
It is also a provincial project of climate change, the project of the exchange of fluorescent lights for efficient bulbs and project mitigation and adaptation, clarified.
At the same table assured Martin Krol, technical advisor to the country 's for climate change, the efforts of China' s was more than is commonly held.
For example, told, greenhouse gas emissions per capita represent in China 6 tons, while in the United States' s 100 tonnes; China is responsible for the 9% of the historical share in the emissions.
It also has developed an unprecedented effort, as regards the use of energy - for example, increased during the last five years of about 20% of the efficiency in energy and expects that by 2020 makes the further progress, he added.
