The world 's plan to rebuild lighting
The UN 's last proposed in Cancun plan for the reconstruction of the domestic lighting, lighting shops and industrial space in 100 countries with a view to limit the greenhouse effect (G), which is almost one third of further restrictions, which is to achieve a Stabilisation climate of the planet from now on by 2020..
This ambitious plan is located in the stage of the large specific projects, which wants to impose the UN in Cancun, in order to compensate for the lack of a difficult for commitments to reduce the industrialised countries.
According to the plan submitted last night, if the incandescent light bulbs, which monopolize the 50 to 70% of the market, will replace bulbs fluokompaktními or, better yet, bulbs with elektroluminiscentními diodes (DEL or `` ice "in English), the quantity of 1.8 billion tons (Gt) Ges emissions on the planet arising out of lighting would odbouralo.
Lighting is responsible for the 8% of the world 's emissions.
It is the equivalent of 70% of the emissions from the vehicle fleet on the planet.
In Copenhagen in the last year, the big countries with a significant proportion of on issues like the United States, China, Europe and other, among them, Canada, engaged in the voluntary plans to reduce, which should allow the decline in global emissions Ges from 53 Gt to 49 Gt.
But it will need to be deducted from this balance of 5 more Gt, to be achieved by 2020, Stabilize heating climate on 2 degrees Celsius in order to exclude, he can not get out of control.
In the incandescent bulbs 95% of the energy is dissipating in the form of heat, and the rest, i. e. 5%, is the product of light.
Having fluokompaktními bulbs, consumption of energy reduces the 75%, and with new light bulbs with DEL, narrow it down this consumption twice more.
Fluokompaktní light bulbs will hold on average from 6000 to 10 000 hours.
The new light bulbs with DEL, such as stated this week in the production of the Philips - this company allegedly participated in the study of the UN - have life expectancy 25 000 hours and consumes about 80% less energy than incandescent light, which gives us an idea of possible savings with a plan of the refund, which would be applied in 100 countries.
All these new light bulbs may also work with reostaty and emit less heat.
And do not contain any mercury.
A few experts have expressed reservations about fluokompaktním light bulbs, because they contain mercury and should be as a sort of hazardous waste, which is still possible in developing countries, unless the producers established a junkyard.
But, as the report says, the main source of mercury emissions on the planet 's fluokompaktní bulb, but rather the thermal coal - fired plants that emit many mercury necessary to produce the electricity wasted in the incandescent bulbs.
Only in the United States of these headquarters put into circulation 25 000 tons of mercury per year.
The report also states in detail the profits from the international programme each country.
For example, Indonesia would save $1 billion a year for the purchase of electricity and eight million tons of CO 2, which is the equivalent of 3,5 thermal power stations, whose construction would cost 2,5 billion
