The rate of unemployment remains in the third quarter in France stable.
Unemployment rate in France, in the sense of the word, according to the International Labour Office (bit) remained stable to 9% in mainland France (9,7%, including overseas areas), as shown provisional data with seasonal variation (CVS), which was published Thursday INSEE.
The number of the unemployed settle at 631 million in the metropolis.
Data from the second quarter were confirmed to 9% of the active population in the metropolis and 9,7%, including overseas areas.
For one year, the unemployment rate increases of 0,1 point.
In the broader picture, 3,4 million people in mainland France in the third quarter is not working, but we wish to work, regardless of whether or not they are available in two weeks, to be able to work, and regardless of whether they are looking for a job or seek.
The current situation of young people in the labour market is still stepped up with a new increase in unemployment rates reaching to 24,2% in mainland France (+ 0,9 point for three months, + 0,5, point for one year) and 25%, including overseas areas.
In the third quarter was in the sense of the word, according to the International Labour Office without work 637 000 young people aged 15 to 24.
As regards the elderly, you have seen in mainland France a slight increase in unemployment on 6,4% in mainland France (+ 0,2 point for three months, as well as per year), that is, 482 000 people from 50 years of higher and 6,6%, including overseas areas.
Only the population aged 25 - 49 years has benefited from the stability of the unemployment rate to 8,3% in mainland France (- 0,1 point for three months, + 0,1 point for one year) and 8,8% in all of France.
Insee has not published monthly unemployment rate since 2006, and that after the argument about the method of calculation.
Eurostat, the statistical agency of the European Union, by contrast, continues in the production of monthly statistics and Tuesday announced peace 9,8% for France (including Dom) in October in September was 9,9%.
